Famiglia Pizzeria, Manhattan, NY  I love it when a bad experience turns into a good one.  We walked past this pizzeria earlier and the scent of the sauce was calling us in. However, we were on our way to review a steakhouse up the block. This was a scheduled review at the steakhouse, and after over 15 minutes waiting for a server to speak to us, we walked out.  We were so hungry, and instantly remembered the pizza place we walked past earlier. We were speed walking to get there, and were surprisingly impressed! How nice it was to walk through the door and be greeted by a warm, "Hello" from the staff behind the counter.  When it comes to pizza there is the crust, the sauce and the cheese (in that order for me). If the crust fails on a pizza, it is like a bad foundation on a house - no good.  This crust was warm, golden, airy, and just the right thickness. When I made the classic pizza fold, I heard the the crunch go straight down the middle. The sauce was classic marinara, lightly seasoned with a ripe summer tomato taste. The cheese was portioned nicely, then when I asked for ground meat topping, my mouth was doing the happy dance as I saw them slather the meat on the slice. No skimping here!  Great dough goes a long way in a pizza parlor. The Stromboli crust was unusually light and crisp. This Stromboli was stuffed with an assortment of Italian meats, sauteed onions, cheese, and seasonings. We dipped it in a side of the marinara sauce and devoured it.  Finally garlic knots!!!! I found that they could have been taken out of the over just a little bit sooner, but the soft chopped garlic on them made them a winner as well.  This place was busy with deliveries going out the door, and people grabbing take out. Seems like all the locals know exactly where to go for their pizza.  We thought we were heading out for steaks. Instead we stumbled on the best little pizza parlor on the upper west side!

The pizza was really bad. I've attended public high school and even the cafeteria pizza is better than this crap. The cheese on the pizza slices was dry and without any taste. The slice itself was dried out. Avoid this branch at all costs!

I believe that this is the original location of the franchise.  I have been eating here since the mid-80s.  The slices are big and the ingredients are good quality.  I go there when I leave Symphony Space or the Thalia. With the hundreds of pizzerias in New York - La Famiglia stands out!
Although they are all over the city, this is my favorite location.  Been going here for years for a quick snack, they also deliver fast.  If you want a good NYC slice of pizza, check them out.
